Historicus 6.98. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>fight, do battle,</b> ἀπὸ τῶν ἵππων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 350a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀπὸ [καμήλων] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 7.1.49 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but ἀφ᾽ ὅτου πολεμήσωμεν what <b>our means of war are,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 3.16. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> generally, <b>quarrel, wrangle with</b> one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.3.11; π. χρείᾳ 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 191 (_anapaest meter_), compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1386; τισὶν ὑπέρ τινος 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.31: _metaphorically_ of disease, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 1.103. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> later with <i>accusative</i>, <b>make war upon,</b> τὴν πόλιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Dinarchus Orator 1.36 codices; τὰς Ἀθήνας 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 4.61, compare 13.84, 14.37, LXX.1Mac.5.30, etc.; τὰς Συρακούσας 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.15.10, etc.: _metaphorically_, τὰς σταφυλάς 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 3.22 \">LXX+4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, also in early writers, <b>have war made upon</b> one, <b>to be treated as enemies,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.37, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 7.4.20; ὑπό τινων 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 5.49; καὶ αὐτοὶ.. ἐκ πολλοῦ πολεμούμενοι 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.43; αὐτὸς μὲν πολεμεῖν ὑμῖν, ὑφ᾽ ὑμῶν δὲ μὴ πολεμεῖσθαι [prev. author] 9.9; -ηθείσης τῆς χώρας “OGI” 748.8 (Cyzicus, 3rd c.BC). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> <i>cognate</i>, πόλεμον π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 551d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], Arist.[same place], etc.:—<i>passive</i>, [πολέμους] τοὺς ἐπὶ Θησέως πολεμηθέντας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.5.10; κατὰ θάλατταν ὁ π. ἐπολεμεῖτο [prev. author] “HG” 5.1.1, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 600a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὅσα ἐπολεμήθη whatever <b>hostilities took place,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 4.1.1; τὰ περὶ Πύλον κατὰ κράτος ἐπολεμεῖτο 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.23, compare 3.6.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —The form used by Poets is πολεμίζω.","strongNumber":"G4170","accentedUnicode":"πολεμέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4171","matchingForm":"πόλεμος","stepTransliteration":"polemos","gloss":"war","_zh_tw_Gloss":"戰, 打仗, 爭戰","_es_Gloss":"guerra","_zh_Gloss":"战, 打仗, 争战"}],"shortDef":"to fight, make war","mediumDef":"to fight, make war <br /><b>to make</b>, or <b>wage war, fight,</b> <ref='Rev.2.16'>Rev. 2:16;</ref> 12:7; <b>to battle, quarrel,</b> <ref='Jas.4.2'>Jas. 4:2</ref>","stepGloss":"to fight","stepTransliteration":"polemeō","count":7,"_es_Definition":"librar guerra, combatir, pelear","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 作戰 <br>2) 為敵, 作對 (雅 4:2)","_zh_Definition":"1) 作战 <br>2) 为敌, 作对 (雅 4:2)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"giao chiến. Xem G4171","_zh_tw_Gloss":"爭戰","_es_Gloss":"pelear","_zh_Gloss":"争战"}]}